Rafael Correa in Quito, this Monday.
Refounding the republic around 21st century socialism.
This is the joint project of Venezuelan Hugo Ch<0xC3><0xA1>vez, Bolivian Evo Morales and Ecuadorian Rafael Correa.
This Sunday, like his colleagues and friends, he is the third to put to the vote a draft for a new Constitution.
Mission accomplished as 64% of voters voted "yes" to the referendum, according to official results referring to 80% of the votes.
According to these results, the "no" got 28%, 7% of the votes were null votes and 0.7% were blank votes.
For the draft Constitution to be adopted, it had to get half the votes plus one.
On Sunday, two polls conducted outside polling stations and a recount by a non-governmental organization had announced a broad "yes" victory, estimating it to be between 63% and 70%.
Rafael Correa had also claimed on the night of Sunday to Monday the victory of his draft Constitution.
The "Constitution triumphed overwhelmingly," he had assured, congratulating the Ecuadorians who head the government of Guayaquil, 280 kilometers southwest of Quito.
Rafael Correa has been congratulated by Ch<0xC3><0xA1>vez and Morales but also by his Chilean colleague Micaela Bachelet.
The elections, which will be held calmly, according to the observation mission of the Organization of American States (OAS), referred to a text of 444 points that consolidated the " new socialism " advocated by the president.
The draft Constitution implies an increase in the State ' s power over the economy, reserving to it the " development planning " of a country that lives essentially through the extraction of oil by foreign companies and through currencies that send their emigrants.
Led by Correa, elected in 2006, the project also grants strengthened powers to the head of state, who will be able to serve up to two consecutive terms of four years each and will have the possibility to dissolve the Assembly.
Correa has already announced that he will use this power and will seek a new mandate in February 2009.
The Constitution further consolidates the principle of free health and education services that the President began to establish in this country of 13.9 million inhabitants, in which 50% of the population lives below the poverty line.
It finally provides for a ban on the presence of foreign troops, which will put an end to the agreement between Quito and Washington for the use of an Ecuadorian base as a starting point for US anti-drug operations.
19 people kidnapped have been released in Chad
An Egyptian commando launched the assault on the kidnappers of the eleven tourists and their eight companions captured ten days ago.
They're in Cairo.
The eleven European tourists and their eight Egyptian companions kidnapped ten days ago in the desert arrived unharmed in the Egyptian capital after being released on Monday afternoon.
In the morning, they had been released by Egyptian special forces in Chad.
All of them looked good upon their arrival at 3:30 p.m. on board a special aircraft at Al Maza military base, adjacent to Cairo International Airport.
Helicopters immediately transported them to Maadi hospital, a residential suburb of Cairo, to undergo medical tests, so they have been unable to speak to the press.
"They are in good health" and "no ransom was paid" to the hijackers, Egyptian Tourism Minister Zoheir Garana said at the airport.
On 19 September these hostages fell into the hands of 35 unknown hijackers while enjoying an off-road safari in a desert area at the foot of Mount Ouanat, on the borders of Egypt, Sudan and Libya, and since then they have moved from one zulu to another.
The group consisted of eleven tourists – five Italians, five Germans and one Romanian – and eight Egyptians: two guides, four drivers, a border guard and the director of the travel agency Aegyptous, in charge of the safari organization.
An Egyptian security official said 30 members of the special forces, carried on board two helicopters, had launched the assault the night before dawn.
"An exchange of shots occurred, and half of the kidnappers were killed, the others have fled," said the official, who remained anonymous.
According to him, 150 members of the Egyptian special forces of the "flashlight" unit were sent to Sudan, where they were supported by German and Italian commands.
The Italian Foreign Minister, Franco Frattini, mentioned in Belgrade the role played by secret agents and by members of the Italian special forces.
"We must recognize that we have achieved this result thanks to the professionalism and effectiveness of our men of the secret services, of the special forces," he said without going into details.
He also denied payment of a ransom.
On the eve of the attack, the Sudanese army claimed to have intercepted during a patrol an all-terrain vehicle on which the kidnappers were on board, of which six were killed, including the Chadian chief and two were detained.
He also claimed that they were related to a Darfur rebel group, the Sudan-Unity Liberation Movement (SLA-U), a claim immediately denied by this group.
Letras - The Silent Majority of Culture
A debate on the financing of culture makes the headlines and occupies the current election campaign.
Better that way.
But a sector of our cultural life remains always forgotten.
Who will stand up to denounce the miserable sums given to small museums, archives, archaeological excavations or national historic sites that starve to death?
Which politician will dare to remind the federal government to neglect its monuments and heritage buildings?
Why don’t we have real laws that effectively preserve our heritage like in Canada and Quebec?
Did you know that the French government is devoting three and a half million euros to restoring only Chinon Castle in the Loire Valley?
In the United States, it is written in its Constitution that the protection of heritage is part of the culture of Americans and that this heritage must be protected by all citizens, all elected and all government departments, and all this, in concert.
In Quebec, in the Federation of Historical Societies of Quebec, at least 40,000 benevolent people regrouped in 211 societies of history, heritage, archives and genealogy are concerned with looking into history, preserving with little money piles of private archives and preserving archaeological remains.
It is these who are often the guardian dogs of our heritage, who protest with energy and despair when promoters and responsible throw their bulldozers against our old stones and our forgotten cemeteries.
For when, a monument to history and heritage?
The governments of the Netherlands nationalize a part of Fortis Bank.
The states of the Netherlands - being the first in Europe - will help with a nationalization of the Belgian-Dutch bank Fortis that is in trouble due to the effect of the mortgage crisis of the North American market: the three countries will support in total with 11.2 billion euros this financial and insurance institution that also has business in Hungary.
This weekend the governments of Belgium, Luxembourg and the Netherlands held consultations at the highest level with the President of the European Central Bank and the European Commission’s Head of Economic Competence.
The Fortis Bank is the first to suffer the euro area crisis in the context of the international financial crisis that has been occurring in several waves for more than a year, therefore the decisions taken with respect to the Bank, in a sense can be considered as precedents.
According to the decision taken in the early hours of Sunday, the three states will buy approximately half (49 percent) of the property owned by the Bank in their area.
The Bank will surely sell a part of its business, including especially the activities - mainly insurance - purchased last year from the Dutch ABN Amr<0xC3><0xB3>.
The shares of Fortis began a sharp decline last week and by the second half of the week there were already important signs of crisis in the institution.
Analysts agree, however, that with its 85,000 employees this bank is too big to allow it to break.
The company's shares fell 12 percent on Friday alone, the lowest point in 14 years.
Since January, the value of the shares has decreased by more than two-thirds.
Looking at the current stock prices, the total value of the group’s capital in the market is around 14 billion euros, but according to the company’s executives this is not real.
The management of the Bank blamed the sharp fall in the shares of Fortis on the insecurities of the US market in connection with the approval of the US $ 700 billion package plan.
On Monday, the shares showed a slight increase.
On Friday, Filip Dierckx was appointed as the bank’s new CEO.
The Bank also looked for private investors, but so far no one has made a concrete offer.
The Belgian government had previously assured that investors did not have to worry, they will not lose their money.
Among the Bank’s clients so far there was no panic, they did not invade the bank offices to withdraw their money.
The Fortis has its own branch in Hungary and has also bought leasing companies.
Fox in the chicken coop
In the U.S., life and health insurance companies often refuse to sign an insurance contract when looking at drug purchase data.
Privacy policy specialists fear that the personal data market will become uncontrollable.
"There are programs for the protection of personal data, which to the use of the recipe data in all cases binds it to the approval of the given person.
The same should be in independent hands, because if not, "we trust the chicken coop to the fox" - quotes the Washington Post to Richard Dick, designer of the program of monitoring medical prescriptions.
Insurance companies make the price of insurance and the amount of compensation depend on the health status of the customer and if they believe that the risk is excessive, they simply do not make the contract.
Previously, they sent the client to medical check-up and signed the contract with him knowing the result of the check-up.
Dick invented a much cheaper procedure ten years ago: with the identification number of the client easily gets from pharmacies the list of drugs purchased in the last year and a half and the program itself draws the conclusion about the diseases and state of health of the client.
For example, if you consistently take large doses of cholesterol-lowering pills, it indicates that your blood fat level is virtually incurably high, so you are immediately included in a higher risk category.
Numerous versions of the program circulate, some even establish a number of risks, so the insurance company in addition to the administration has little to do, although there are small difficulties in this regard.
Among the disadvantages of the program is, for example, that some drugs are multipurpose, for example, certain substances serve both to treat headache and for heat waves and even as antidepressants.
The latter is a major risk factor for insurance companies while the former do not.
Special companies were set up to consult and process this data, which, before acquiring the necessary information from pharmacies, require the approval of the patient.
The authorities are already forcing them to do this, although they have not been fined for negligence so far.
Some companies have recently also developed the results of laboratory tests and by combining them with drug consumption data they get more accurate information about the patient’s health status.
More and more companies have access to this data and at the same time it is increasingly difficult to control its use.
There is an exclusive law for the protection of personal health data, but it applies only to insurance companies and those that provide health services.
The bill that gives the right to the authority to control specialized companies for the provision of personal data is already before Congress.
Dick Richard recognizes that this is insufficient: therefore he developed his program, which will require the specific approval of the person for the provision of his own personal data.
It is another matter that such a person cannot deny his approval, because if not the insurance companies will not sign the contract with him.
So that the hens, despite everything, are exposed to the good will of the fox.
